               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1382" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1382" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1382" type="surname" value="BLAIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1382" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE"></interp>CHARLOTTE BLAIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Samuel Blain, we lodge in a first-floor in Devonshire-street, at a coffee-shop—the prisoner used fre<lb></lb>quently to come there of a morning for about ten minutes, to have her coffee—she was there on the afternoon of the 3rd of April—I saw her go into the yard—I was in the back parlour—my room door was shut when I left it, but not locked—my property was safe—I was absent about an hour and a half, and when I returned I found the room stripped of all the property—the two-penny piece had been in a little box in the drawer that the clothes were taken out of—it was a two-penny copper-piece—I saw the prisoner again the same evening at the station-house, about two hours after I lost my property—I have lost all my property except the two-penny piece—it was not locked in the drawer, but the little box was—I had seen her at the shop that evening.</p>
               <p>
